title: For Sale:  250 Grain Barnes 308 bullets for reloading
postcontent: I have 30 of the original Barnes, 250 grain, round nose, jacketed bullets for reloading.  These were designed for grizzly and African game for .308 caliber rifles.  They have not been made in about 20 years and the heaviest 30 cal bullets available today are the Woodleigh 220 grain which sell for about $2 each, but simply cannot penetrate like these  250 grain pills.  I have hoarded a couple boxes for more than 20 years for use in my 300 Weaherby and 30-06 for when I go to Wyoming in grizzly country.
